# E-Commerce Domain Standard

## Purpose

Define the e-commerce domain architecture for the enterprise platform.

This rule establishes bounded contexts, integration patterns, and commerce-wide invariants that all feature rules inherit.

---

## Business Scope

The platform supports:

- B2C online retail (primary)
- Multi-currency transactions
- Guest and registered checkout
- Product catalog with variants and categories
- Real-time inventory management
- Stripe payment processing
- Order lifecycle and fulfillment tracking
- Promotional discounts (extensible)

Out of scope unless explicitly requested:

- Marketplace multi-vendor splits
- Subscription billing (requires ADR)
- Physical POS integration

---

## Bounded Contexts

```
┌─────────────┐     ┌─────────────┐     ┌─────────────┐
│   Catalog   │────▶│  Inventory  │◀────│   Checkout  │
└─────────────┘     └─────────────┘     └──────┬──────┘
       │                    │                   │
       │              ┌─────▼─────┐       ┌─────▼─────┐
       │              │  Orders   │◀──────│ Payments  │
       │              └───────────┘       └───────────┘
       │                    │
┌──────▼──────┐      ┌──────▼──────┐
│  Customers  │      │ Fulfillment │
└─────────────┘      └─────────────┘
```

| Context | Aggregate Roots | Responsibility |
|---------|-------------------|----------------|
| Catalog | Product, Category | Merchandising, pricing display |
| Inventory | InventoryItem, Reservation | Stock levels, holds |
| Checkout | Cart, CheckoutSession | Pre-purchase flow |
| Orders | Order | Post-purchase lifecycle |
| Payments | PaymentRecord | Stripe integration, reconciliation |
| Customers | Customer, Address | Identity, shipping/billing |

Each context owns its data and business rules. Cross-context communication uses application services, domain events, or anti-corruption layers — never direct table access across modules.

---

## Context Integration Map

| Upstream | Downstream | Pattern | Contract |
|----------|------------|---------|----------|
| Catalog | Checkout | Published language | Product/variant ID + price snapshot |
| Inventory | Checkout | Customer/supplier | Reserve/release API |
| Checkout | Orders | Process manager | Place order command |
| Checkout | Payments | Process manager | Create payment intent |
| Payments | Orders | Event | Payment succeeded → confirm order |
| Orders | Inventory | Event | Confirm → deduct reserved stock |
| Customers | Checkout | Shared kernel | Customer ID, addresses |

Document new integrations with context mapping (`architecture/01-ddd`).

